						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Āmalakēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja III. Year 31: 1246-47 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and incomplete inscription seems to record a grant of land to god Tirunellikkāvuḍaiyār by Arayaṉ Tillaiperumāṉ of Tiṭṭaichchēri and his brothers Ga[ṇḍarā dittadē]vaṉ and Uyyavandāṉ. It also mentions the land of a certain Tamiḻavēḷāṉ (see No. 567 above) as the western boundary of apparently the granted land.</p>						

						<p>Read <hi rend="grantha">saṅjñ</hi><ta>aiyāṉamaikku.</ta></p>						

						</summary>
